{
  "question_id": "question-008",
  "title": "Large Counts Condition",
  "difficulty": "Moderate",
  "question_text": "<div class=\"paragraph\">Why is it important to check the large counts condition when dealing with sampling distributions of the sample proportion, <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$\\hat{p}$</span>?</div>",
  "image_files": [],
  "choices": [
    {
      "letter": "A",
      "text": "To ensure the sample is large enough"
    },
    {
      "letter": "B",
      "text": "To be ensure that each trial is independent from each other"
    },
    {
      "letter": "C",
      "text": "To be able to use the standard deviation of the sampling distribution of\n^\np"
    },
    {
      "letter": "D",
      "text": "To ensure that the usage of the normal approximation is a appropriate"
    },
    {
      "letter": "E",
      "text": "In order to use the mean of the sampling distribution of\n^\np"
    }
  ],
  "correct_answer": "<strong>Choice 'D'</strong> is the correct answer. ",
  "solution": "When dealing with sampling distributions, the shape of the distribution can vary from one to another. In order to ensure that we can use the normal approximation when dealing with inference problems for the sample proportion, <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17060-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mrow class=&quot;MJX-TeXAtom-ORD&quot;><mover><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;>&amp;#x005E;</mo></mover></mrow></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91499\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91500\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91501\" class=\"mjx-texatom\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91502\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91503\" class=\"mjx-munderover\"><span class=\"mjx-stack\"><span class=\"mjx-over\" style=\"height: 0.213em; padding-bottom: 0.06em; padding-left: 0.085em;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91505\" class=\"mjx-mo\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">^</span></span></span><span class=\"mjx-op\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91504\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.222em; padding-bottom: 0.496em;\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\"><mover><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">^</mo></mover></mrow></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17060\">\\hat{p}</script></span>, we must first check the Large Counts Condition, \n\n<span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17061-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mi>n</mi><mi>p</mi><mo>&amp;#x2265;</mo><mn>10</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91506\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91507\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91508\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.222em; padding-bottom: 0.277em;\">n</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91509\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.222em; padding-bottom: 0.496em;\">p</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91510\" class=\"mjx-mo MJXc-space3\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.332em; padding-bottom: 0.496em;\">≥</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91511\" class=\"mjx-mn MJXc-space3\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">10</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mi>p</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>10</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17061\">np \\geq 10</script></span>\n\nand\n\n<span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17062-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&amp;#x2212;</mo><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;>)</mo><mo>&amp;#x2265;</mo><mn>10</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91512\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91513\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91514\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.222em; padding-bottom: 0.277em;\">n</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91515\" class=\"mjx-mo\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.606em;\">(</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91516\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">1</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91517\" class=\"mjx-mo MJXc-space2\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.277em; padding-bottom: 0.441em;\">−</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91518\" class=\"mjx-mi MJXc-space2\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.222em; padding-bottom: 0.496em;\">p</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91519\" class=\"mjx-mo\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.606em;\">)</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91520\" class=\"mjx-mo MJXc-space3\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.332em; padding-bottom: 0.496em;\">≥</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91521\" class=\"mjx-mn MJXc-space3\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">10</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>−</mo><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>≥</mo><mn>10</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17062\">n(1-p) \\geq 10</script></span>\n\nIf both of these conditions are true, then we can apply the normal approximation to our inference problem. \n\n<strong>Choice 'D'</strong> is correct. ",
  "distractor_explanations": {
    "A": "<strong>Choice 'A'</strong> is incorrect. When dealing with proportions, we simply need to ensure that the expected number of success and expected number of failures are both at least 10. If we were doing a problem regarding means, then we would have to check the <strong>Central Limit Theorem</strong>, which the sample size must be larger than <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17063-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>30</mn></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91522\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91523\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91524\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">30</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17063\">30</script></span>. ",
    "B": "<strong>Choice 'B'</strong> is incorrect. To check for independence from one trial to another, you must check the <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17064-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>10</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91525\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91526\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91527\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">10</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91528\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17064\">10\\%</script></span> condition, not the Large Counts Condition. ",
    "C": "<strong>Choice 'C'</strong> is incorrect. In order to use the standard deviation of the sampling distribution for <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17065-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mrow class=&quot;MJX-TeXAtom-ORD&quot;><mover><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;>&amp;#x005E;</mo></mover></mrow></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91529\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91530\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91531\" class=\"mjx-texatom\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91532\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91533\" class=\"mjx-munderover\"><span class=\"mjx-stack\"><span class=\"mjx-over\" style=\"height: 0.213em; padding-bottom: 0.06em; padding-left: 0.085em;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91535\" class=\"mjx-mo\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">^</span></span></span><span class=\"mjx-op\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91534\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.222em; padding-bottom: 0.496em;\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\"><mover><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">^</mo></mover></mrow></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17065\">\\hat{p}</script></span>, you must check the <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17066-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>10</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91536\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91537\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91538\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">10</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91539\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17066\">10\\%</script></span> condition, not the Large Counts Condition. ",
    "E": "<strong>Choice 'E'</strong> is incorrect. The mean does not require a condition to be checked. The mean of the sampling distribution of <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17067-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mrow class=&quot;MJX-TeXAtom-ORD&quot;><mover><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;>&amp;#x005E;</mo></mover></mrow></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91540\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91541\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91542\" class=\"mjx-texatom\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91543\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91544\" class=\"mjx-munderover\"><span class=\"mjx-stack\"><span class=\"mjx-over\" style=\"height: 0.213em; padding-bottom: 0.06em; padding-left: 0.085em;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91546\" class=\"mjx-mo\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">^</span></span></span><span class=\"mjx-op\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91545\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.222em; padding-bottom: 0.496em;\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\"><mover><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">^</mo></mover></mrow></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17067\">\\hat{p}</script></span> simply use the formula <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17068-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><msub><mi>&amp;#x03BC;</mi><mrow class=&quot;MJX-TeXAtom-ORD&quot;><mover><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=&quot;false&quot;>&amp;#x005E;</mo></mover></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91547\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91548\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91549\" class=\"mjx-msubsup\"><span class=\"mjx-base\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91550\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.222em; padding-bottom: 0.496em;\">μ</span></span></span><span class=\"mjx-sub\" style=\"font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.24em; padding-right: 0.071em;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91551\" class=\"mjx-texatom\" style=\"\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91552\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91553\" class=\"mjx-munderover\"><span class=\"mjx-stack\"><span class=\"mjx-over\" style=\"height: 0.213em; padding-bottom: 0.06em; padding-left: 0.085em;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91555\" class=\"mjx-mo\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">^</span></span></span><span class=\"mjx-op\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91554\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.222em; padding-bottom: 0.496em;\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91556\" class=\"mjx-mo MJXc-space3\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.058em; padding-bottom: 0.332em;\">=</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91557\" class=\"mjx-mi MJXc-space3\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I\" style=\"padding-top: 0.222em; padding-bottom: 0.496em;\">p</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>μ</mi><mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\"><mover><mi>p</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">^</mo></mover></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17068\">\\mu_\\hat{p} = p</script></span>"
